description:
&lt;p&gt;We are a busy innovative practice working across 2 sites with a patient population of 7000 and we are looking for a Healthcare Assistant (HCA) to join our friendly team. This position is part-time hours (up to 16 p/week) to be undertaken flexibly between 2-4 days and so would be suitable for a parent of school age children.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our practice requires a qualified HCA to undertake general HCA duties including venepuncture (essential), immunisations, ear irrigation, health promotion, wound management, long-term condition management (see job description for more details). Some previous experience is required, although on-the-job training will be provided to increase skills for the right candidate and this role may suit a phlebotomist looking to expand their role. Agreed salary will reflect the current skills and experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We believe in enabling people to take control of their health care journeys – we help to change the way health and wellbeing services work so care can focus on what matters to individuals. There may be opportunities to work with other practices through collaboration in the area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact Lindsay.coleman@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Here are committed to equality and valuing diversity.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
